Danish Superliga champions FC Copenhagen have ruled out Akinkunmi Amoo indefinitely due to an injury he sustained earlier this month. The Super Eagles star has had a difficult start to the week, as he also failed to make the ten-man shortlist for the CAF young player of the year award.   Raheem Sterling confirms Man City departure before Chelsea…     Leeds United agree deal with Barcelona for Raphinha     Lewandowski begins pre-season training at Bayern Munich   And according to a statement by his club, Amoo will be out of action indefinitely due to injury. Amoo’s injury comes at a bad time, as since his move from Hammarby to Copenhagen in January, 20-year-old has failed to justify the €4.5 million that was paid for his services. The Nigerian forward struggled to get playtime last season, and the preseason was supposed to be the best time for him to get fully integrated into the team.